Description: HepBee uses technology to increase patient safety and prevent Hepatitis B (HBV) infection.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: HepBee is a mobile application designed to minimize the risk of HBV seroconversion in hemodialysis patients. Hemodialysis patients are at an increased risk for Hepatitis B seroconversion due to the opportunity for exposure during treatment and weakened immune systems. Seroconversion and prevalence rates have greatly declined since the 1970s when the first practice patterns and protocols to reduce the spread of HBV were mandated by the CDC. However, HBV is still of concern and outbreaks continue to occur. According to the CDC, “Investigations of these outbreaks have documented that HBV transmission resulted from failure to use recommended infection control practices, including: a) failure to routinely screen patients for HBsAg or routinely review results of testing to identify infected patients b) assignment of staff members to the simultaneous care of infected and susceptible patients c) sharing of supplies, particularly multiple dose medication vials, among patients Prevalence and seroconversion rates often differ facility-to-facility even with prevention protocols in place. HepBee addresses aspects of the practice failures that the CDC identified and ensures the successful practice patterns are being followed consistently and accurately by every staff member at every facility for every patient contact. HepBee interprets the complex Hepatitis B serological tests and guides the user to use correct protocols to reduce the incidence of HBV in hemodialysis patients.

Description: Games Production Studio
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: React Entertainment was a games studio focused on transforming classical 2D animation into an interactive gaming experience. The company focused its efforts on porting the classic arcade game "The Act" from its prior video arcade architecture to a game that functioned on iOS and OSX  "The Act", a completely hand-drawn first-person adventure, was billed as the world’s First Interactive Cinematic Game - wherein the player could guide guides a hand-drawn character’s personality, emotions and behaviors. The game storyline, played out across a number of movie-like scenes, was accompanied by a classical musical score.  After founding and beginning development in 2009, React signed a distribution deal with Chillingo (Electronic Arts) in 2011, and launched a paid version of the iOS version of the game in June of 2012, followed closely by a version for OSX in August of the same year. A further "Freemium" version was released in February of 2013, providing access to a wider audience.  In distribution terms, the game achieved the position of #4 on the US Apple Gamestore, and #13 on the overall Appstore. The Act was nominated for IMGA awards in several categories, including excellence in visuals, gameplay, and storytelling. It was also nominated as "Best in Category" in the Casual Gameplay 2012 awards, and won It won "Most Innovative Game 2012" from Best App Ever Awards. After a successful commercial run from 2011-2014, the game was with withdrawn from the Appstore in early 2015, and the company shut down.
Founders: Alain Laferriere, Daniel Kraus, Jean Laferriere, Omar Khudari

Headquarters Regions: Greater Phoenix Area, Western US
Full Description: We give consumers a $250 Visa gift card when they match with real estate or mortgage professional on our site. Professionals in the real estate/mortgage industry spend a lot of time and money trying to find new clients. Real Estate Ready brings the client to them by reverse prospecting. This process also puts more control in the hands of the consumer. On oursite people can look over any professional’s bio, read reviews from their past clients and even watch a short video from the agent. This convenient review process allows people to screen and select professionals anytime, from their phone or PC. We only ask that people are ready to buy or sell before they search and connect with a proffesional. Before allowing a buyer to be matched with a buyers agent we look to make sure that they are pre-qualified. If the potential buyer is not pre-qualified, they will be given the option of selecting a mortgage professional on our site and receive an additional gift card. RE Ready data - will be able to produce a snapshot of projected sales. Knowing where people intend to sell before they list or where people intend to buy before they make a purchase, we can produce a live picture of what is happening in the market at any given time. Much like a fish-finder, we can see where the action is, not where it was. We will be able to offer forecasting data never seen in the industry before. We bring new technology to the public giving them a better way to find a professional. Our business improves the overall consumers experience when it comes to buying, selling or picking a professional to work with. We also revolutionize the way real estate agents and mortgage professionals find new clients, convert leads and market themselves. Bottom line, our service is unique, revolutionary, recession proof and in line with today’s tech market! People are going to buy or sell real estate. The question is, do you think they’re not going to want to get paid to do it?

Companies post a case. This case may be a real time problem or opportunity that they are experiencing. Students then compete to come up with the best solution and submit this solution to the company. After the submission deadline, companies evaluate solutions and choose a winner. This winner receives a prize of $100 and any additional offering by the company.    Students receive the chance to get noticed for a job opportunity, cash, experience, and a tangible portfolio. Description: Panasonic Weather Solutions has developed and deployed TAMDAR on more than 300 aircraft.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: Panasonic Weather Solutions has developed and deployed TAMDAR on more than 300 aircraft. What makes TAMDAR unique is that it captures temperature, pressure, winds aloft, icing, turbulence and relative humidity, bundles the data with GPS (Global Positioning System) data and transmits the information, in real-time, over satellite networks. Like the data traditionally gathered by worldwide weather balloons, this information is used to update weather models. Unlike weather balloons, TAMDAR collects the data continuously and in real-time. TAMDAR technology is protected by several U.S. and worldwide patents, and the relative humidity data, gathered throughout an aircraft’s flight, makes these weather soundings particularly valuable to meteorologists.
